wikipedia_page.main: William Austin (born 1801) was an English first-class cricketer active in 1827 and 1828. He was born in Cambridge.Austin made two first-class appearances for the Cambridge Union Club, with both appearances coming against Cambridge University in 1827 and 1828 at the University Ground, Barnwell. Austin scored a total of 59 runs in his two matches, top scoring with 35.
